First, `do while` block first executes the entire body of `do` statement and then checks for the condition in the `while` statement. There is `for` loop inside the `do` block, which will run to its entirety and then the `while` loop&#39;s condition will be evaluated. Because of this `for` loop you are unable to exit the game when user has guessed the word correctly.&lt;br/&gt;
Second, the exit condition in while block is also incorrect. It will continue to run until both the conditions, `attempts&lt;maxattempts` and `!checkIfCorrect` evaluates to false. What you want is to exit the block once either one of the condition fails. Basically it should be replaced with `attempts &lt; maxattempts &amp;&amp; !checkifcorrect`&lt;br/&gt;
